text: Tinea dividua is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Alfred Philpott in 1928. However the placement of this species within the genus Tinea is in doubt. As a result, this species has been referred to as Tinea (s.l.) dividua. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== ==External links== *Image of type specimen of Tinea s.l. dividua.
